		<tr>
			<td><b>Senior Vice President and Chief Operating Officer,&nbsp;Comcast Media Center</b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Traver_Gary.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Gary Traver is Senior Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of Comcast Media Center (CMC), which provides multiplatform content development and distribution solutions for cable system operators and the content community, including TV networks, independent producers, advertisers and retailers.<br><br>
Traver, who was named COO in 2003, had served as Senior Vice President and General Manager of the CMC since its acquisition by Comcast in the Fall of 2002.  Prior to the acquisition, he was Senior Vice President of Video Services for the CMC, formerly AT&T Digital Media Centers, since joining the company in 1999.<br><br>
Prior to joining AT&T Digital Media Centers, Traver served as Vice President of Broadcast and Network Operations for PRIMESTAR, which later became DirecTV. In that role, he was responsible for creation, operation and management of the direct broadcast satellite network and his team received an EMMY award for their pioneering work in digital television.<br><br>
The 25-year industry veteran also held senior-level assignments at Skyband, Inc., and Comsat Satellite Television. He is actively involved in SMPTE, SCTE and the NCTA Technology Committee and serves on the Board of Directors for Combined Conditional Access Development and Support, LLC (CCAD), and on SES AMERICOM’s Customer Advisory Board.
  

</td>
		
		
